truth... my own father abandoned me

257
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:31,800
We actually did it.We made it

258
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,060
It's just as I remember in my dreams

259
00:16:38,500 --> 00:16:39,520
Hasn't changed at all

260
00:16:41,160 --> 00:16:42,080
It's beautiful

261
00:16:42,380 --> 00:16:44,130
No,it's more than that

262
00:16:44,520 --> 00:16:45,650
Neverland is special

263
00:16:45,820 --> 00:16:46,860
You can do anything here

264
00:16:47,210 --> 00:16:48,940
Just think it,and it can happen

265
00:16:50,910 --> 00:16:51,970
What would you like to eat

266
00:16:52,310 --> 00:16:54,230
Go on.Just think it

267
00:17:02,110 --> 00:17:04,880
You can eat cake all day
and not get a stomachache

268
00:17:05,740 --> 00:17:07,750
Or swing on a vine through a waterfall

269
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:12,980
But best of all... you can fly

270
00:17:13,610 --> 00:17:14,730
Flying is impossible

271
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:18,390
Neverland is where the impossible
is possible, if you believe it

272
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:20,560
Here,I'll show you

273
00:17:35,210 --> 00:17:35,900
I don't understand

274
00:17:40,350 --> 00:17:42,400
I could always fly
when I visited as a boy

275
00:17:43,090 --> 00:17:46,220
Maybe you can't fly because
you're not a boy anymore

276
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:48,510
How could I have forgotten

277
00:17:50,080 --> 00:17:50,980
Of course

278
00:17:52,130 --> 00:17:53,200
Pixie dust

279
00:17:55,220 --> 00:17:58,890
Even as a boy,you needed
pixie dust if you wanted to fly

280
00:18:00,030 --> 00:18:04,600
- Where do we get some?
- Oh,I'll show you

281
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:27,400
Hey,Wendy, since you've been
here,have you seen my son

282
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,210
His name's Henry

283
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:31,410
- You have a son
- Yeah

284
00:18:32,460 --> 00:18:33,740
Pan needs his heart

285
00:18:34,290 --> 00:18:36,650
Has he said anything about the
heart of the truest believer

286
00:18:37,430 --> 00:18:39,880
No I'm sorry

287
00:18:41,140 --> 00:18:42,600
He never mentioned
anything about a heart

288
00:18:43,010 --> 00:18:43,600
She's lying

289
00:18:45,610 --> 00:18:47,150
Where is he

290
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:47,970
What the hell are you doing

291
00:18:48,300 --> 00:18:51,760
I've carried enough lies in my
life to recognize their burden

292
00:18:51,940 --> 00:18:53,410
She knows where Henry is

293
00:18:55,470 --> 00:18:56,220
Is that true

294
00:18:59,140 --> 00:19:00,300
You don't understand

295
00:19:00,730 --> 00:19:01,820
You're helping Pan

296
00:19:02,280 --> 00:19:06,570
He's keeping John and Michael
alive, only if I do as he says

297
00:19:06,720 --> 00:19:09,900
Trust me, whatever he's
promised,he will go back on his word

298
00:19:10,150 --> 00:19:12,610
And why should I trust a
man who abandoned his own son

299
00:19:12,880 --> 00:19:14,100
Because your brothers did

300
00:19:15,630 --> 00:19:17,130
They trusted a woman named Belle

301
00:19:17,950 --> 00:19:21,730
They helped her get this
box so we can defeat Pan

302
00:19:22,310 --> 00:19:23,070
They're okay

303
00:19:23,420 --> 00:19:26,830
For now, and only if we succeed

304
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:32,420
Wendy... we will save John
and Michael,I swear to God

305
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:38,400
But right now,I really
need your help.Please

306
00:19:41,490 --> 00:19:45,680
Pan told Henry that... he
needs his heart to save magic

307
00:19:47,480 --> 00:19:48,420
But it's a lie

308
00:19:50,100 --> 00:19:51,870
He needs it to save himself

309
00:19:52,340 --> 00:19:53,230
What do you mean

310
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:55,690
Pan's dying

311
00:19:56,850 --> 00:20:01,330
He needs the heart of the truest believer
to absorb all the magic in Neverland

312
00:20:01,910 --> 00:20:07,040
And once he does... he will
be immortal,all powerful

313
00:20:08,390 --> 00:20:09,780
And what happens to Henry

314
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:13,360
Well,it's a trade

315
00:20:14,590 --> 00:20:18,380
When Pan lives, Henry will die

316
00:20:54,570 --> 00:20:57,310
Ah,it's been a long time since
I stepped foot on this shore

317
00:21:06,300 --> 00:21:07,260
What's that

318
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:09,610
It's a protection spell

319
00:21:11,660 --> 00:21:13,810
Now let's go.It's time

320
00:21:27,420 --> 00:21:28,200
How do we stop Pan

321
00:21:28,760 --> 00:21:30,090
Pan took Henry to Skull Rock

322
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:31,710
But you haven't got much time

323
00:21:33,180 --> 00:21:33,980
Then we stay behind

324
00:21:34,330 --> 00:21:36,960
Someone needs to be here to guard
the lost boys when they wake up

325
00:21:37,180 --> 00:21:38,800
- You don't need to stay behind
- David's right

326
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:40,910
You get him home,tell him we love him

327
00:21:42,060 --> 00:21:44,420
Tell him yourself, when you
get back from Deadman's Peak

328
00:21:45,740 --> 00:21:47,360
Gold can cure you back in Storybrooke

329
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:48,700
We just need to bring
some of the water with us

330
00:21:53,780 --> 00:21:59,450
And you... you didn't give up.Thank you

331
00:21:59,950 --> 00:22:02,070
Well,apparently,that's the
only thanks I need these days

332
00:22:02,530 --> 00:22:04,070
Tink and I will take care of things here

333
00:22:04,450 --> 00:22:06,410
Meet you back at the "Jolly
Roger" when you find Henry

334
00:22:07,210 --> 00:22:09,510
Promise me if your father and I
don't make it back,you get him home

335
00:22:09,780 --> 00:22:12,760
We're all going back home.Together

336
00:22:27,110 --> 00:22:27,820
I'm tired

337
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:29,910
We're almost there

338
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:32,610
We can rest all we want
after we get the pixie dust,

339
00:22:32,880 --> 00:22:34,160
do whatever your heart desires

340
00:22:34,420 --> 00:22:35,450
Just wait.You'll see

341
00:22:36,990 --> 00:22:38,000
What does it look like

342
00:22:39,560 --> 00:22:40,540
It's just like dust

343
00:22:41,690 --> 00:22:43,920
You never know the power it
contains just by looking at it

344
00:22:44,320 --> 00:22:45,570
But when you believe in its power,

345
00:22:45,750 --> 00:22:48,550
it glows with magic and becomes
something very special indeed

346
00:22:53,780 --> 00:22:55,390
We're here

347
00:22:56,330 --> 00:22:57,430
All I see are trees

348
00:22:59,170 --> 00:23:02,220
That's because it's made in the flowers
that grow on the highest of the branches

349
00:23:02,590 --> 00:23:04,220
Where they're closest to the stars

350
00:23:04,430 --> 00:23:06,730
The flowers bloom at
night,soak in the starlight

351
00:23:07,340 --> 00:23:09,000
That's how the pixie dust gets its magic

352
00:23:10,600 --> 00:23:12,300
I haven't felt this excited in years,

353
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:16,590
since I was a boy about to climb
one of those trees in my dreams

354
00:23:19,570 --> 00:23:20,920
Come on,Rumple

355
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:22,580
It'll be fun

356
00:23:24,160 --> 00:23:28,590
Hey... you wanna fly,you
can't be afraid of heights

357
00:23:28,820 --> 00:23:31,340
But I don't want to fly.You do

358
00:23:32,050 --> 00:23:35,050
But you will,son, once
you see how it feels

359
00:23:37,610 --> 00:23:40,750
The wind whipping in your
hair,the world below you

360
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:42,770
Like you've not got a care in the world

361
00:23:43,190 --> 00:23:46,230
You're all alone.You're free

362
00:23:49,330 --> 00:23:51,840
Come on,I'll give you a boost

363
00:23:52,080 --> 00:23:52,920
But what if I fall

364
00:23:53,650 --> 00:23:54,920
I promise you won't,hey

365
00:23:55,190 --> 00:23:59,610
Don't make me,papa Please.I'm scared

366
00:24:02,410 --> 00:24:03,940
I'm sorry,Rumple

367
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:05,560
I just get excited

368
00:24:06,240 --> 00:24:09,060
Why don't you wait here,and I'll go get
the pixie dust for the both of us,hmm

369
00:24:14,010 --> 00:24:16,430
- You promise not to be long
- Aye

370
00:24:17,520 --> 00:24:18,490
I'll be as quick as a whip

371
00:24:18,730 --> 00:24:19,790
Back before you know it

372
00:24:20,990 --> 00:24:24,040
And then you'll see how
wonderful Neverland can really be

373
00:25:08,740 --> 00:25:10,030
I want to fly

374
00:25:22,940 --> 00:25:23,640
Hello

375
00:25:25,680 --> 00:25:26,560
Is someone there

376
00:25:34,230 --> 00:25:34,990
Who are you

377
00:25:35,280 --> 00:25:38,860
I am the sole inhabitant of Neverland

378
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:40,310
Then can you tell me what's wrong

379
00:25:42,090 --> 00:25:43,480
Why can't I fly

380
00:25:43,990 --> 00:25:45,970
You have to believe

381
00:25:46,160 --> 00:25:47,900
I'm trying,but it doesn't work

382
00:25:48,070 --> 00:25:50,750
Because you don't belong

383
00:25:56,610 --> 00:26:03,920
Papa.Papa.Papa

384
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:24,520
These are Henry's shoes

385
00:26:27,530 --> 00:26:28,470
Wendy was right

386
00:26:29,130 --> 00:26:29,980
They're here

387
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:33,000
Are you okay

388
00:26:33,560 --> 00:26:34,370
I think so

389
00:26:35,360 --> 00:26:36,290
What was that

390
00:26:36,560 --> 00:26:38,020
Pan cast a protection spell

391
00:26:38,320 --> 00:26:39,800
There has to be a way to break it

392
00:26:44,630 --> 00:26:45,600
Careful with that

393
00:26:46,260 --> 00:26:49,160
Try all you want,but
Pan's magic is too powerful

394
00:26:49,430 --> 00:26:50,250
At least for you

395
00:26:54,980 --> 00:26:57,050
Wha... How did you do that

396
00:26:57,250 --> 00:27:00,370
The spell is designed to keep anyone
who casts a shadow from entering

397
00:27:00,590 --> 00:27:01,550
And you don't have one

398
00:27:02,020 --> 00:27:04,290
You were telling the truth
about ripping your shadow off

399
00:27:04,800 --> 00:27:05,700
And Pan knows it

400
00:27:06,970 --> 00:27:08,500
That's why he cast the spell he did

401
00:27:09,240 --> 00:27:10,820
This isn't about keeping you out

402
00:27:11,090 --> 00:27:12,200
It's about drawing me in

403
00:27:12,910 --> 00:27:15,510
He knows I won't give up the chance
to finish what I came here to do

404
00:27:15,900 --> 00:27:17,440
You really did come here to save Henry

405
00:27:18,080 --> 00:27:19,780
I gave you my trust with that box

406
00:27:20,990 --> 00:27:22,770
Now I need you to give it back

407
00:27:32,970 --> 00:27:34,260
You better come through,Gold

408
00:27:34,420 --> 00:27:37,340
Or I'll make whatever Pan has
planned for you look like child's play

409
00:27:38,980 --> 00:27:40,020
You understand me

410
00:27:41,550 --> 00:27:45,030
Well,a simple "good
luck" would've sufficed

411
00:28:04,860 --> 00:28:06,090
So what are we supposed to do now

412
00:28:06,280 --> 00:28:08,900
What about the spell my father
used to rip off his shadow

413
00:28:09,140 --> 00:28:12,000
You think if I knew how to do that,
I wouldn't have done it already

414
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:17,580
- The moon
- The moon

415
00:28:17,940 --> 00:28:19,850
The moon is what
causes our shadows,right

416
00:28:20,560 --> 00:28:22,790
What if there was a way
to block it out using magic

417
00:28:23,860 --> 00:28:25,060
What,you mean like an eclipse

418
00:28:25,220 --> 00:28:26,030
Is that even possible

419
00:28:26,200 --> 00:28:26,950
- Maybe
- So

420
00:28:27,520 --> 00:28:29,490
- I need help
- With magic

421
00:28:31,020 --> 00:28:32,400
It requires a lot

422
00:28:33,560 --> 00:28:36,260
I guess we're about to find out how
much those lessons I gave you paid off

423
00:28:38,250 --> 00:28:39,660
Follow my lead

424
00:29:05,940 --> 00:29:06,800
This is it

425
00:29:07,520 --> 00:29:09,470
The place where you're
going to save magic

426
00:29:10,020 --> 00:29:11,130
Why does it have to be here

427
00:29:11,670 --> 00:29:14,950
Well,because this is the location
from which Neverland's magic emanates

428
00:29:18,610 --> 00:29:19,810
What's the hourglass for

429
00:29:20,250 --> 00:29:23,680
Marks how much time we have left
before Neverland's magic runs out

430
00:29:24,190 --> 00:29:25,110
It's almost empty

431
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:33,630
- Is something wrong?
- No.Come with me

432
00:29:39,900 --> 00:29:43,460
There's something I need to take
care of before we get started,okay

433
00:30:09,010 --> 00:30:09,750
What's wrong

434
00:30:10,770 --> 00:30:13,160
- Rumple
- Papa

435
00:30:15,430 --> 00:30:17,000
I thought something
terrible had happened to you

436
00:30:17,830 --> 00:30:20,170
No.No,I'm fine,son

437
00:30:21,520 --> 00:30:22,950
You don't have to worry about me

438
00:30:28,730 --> 00:30:29,930
Did you get pixie dust

439
00:30:32,270 --> 00:30:32,940
Yes

440
00:30:33,540 --> 00:30:36,040
But when I tried using it,it didn't work

441
00:30:36,560 --> 00:30:37,420
Why not

442
00:30:38,850 --> 00:30:39,870
I'm not a boy anymore

443
00:30:40,640 --> 00:30:41,460
You were right

444
00:30:42,110 --> 00:30:43,610
Neverland is just for children

445
00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:45,810
Adults don't belong here

446
00:30:46,160 --> 00:30:50,040
Then... we'll leave
and go somewhere else

447
00:30:50,860 --> 00:30:55,830
All that matters...
is that we're together

448
00:30:57,530 --> 00:30:58,770
I wish it was that easy

449
00:30:59,590 --> 00:31:04,490
But we both know wherever we
go, I'll go back to my old ways

450
00:31:05,960 --> 00:31:07,960
I can never be the
father you need me to be

451
00:31:10,630 --> 00:31:13,640
- I'm too weak 
- I don't understand

452
00:31:15,950 --> 00:31:17,230
What are you trying to say

453
00:31:19,350 --> 00:31:21,320
That there is a way
that I can stay here,

454
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:25,320
a way that I can get the pixie
dust to work so I can fly again...

455
00:31:26,060 --> 00:31:27,800
just like I was when I was a boy

456
00:31:28,620 --> 00:31:29,240
How

457
00:31:31,310 --> 00:31:35,580
By letting go of the thing
that is holding me back... you

458
00:31:38,160 --> 00:31:39,760
Help!A monster

459
00:31:41,510 --> 00:31:43,860
It's not a monster,Rumple.It's a friend

460
00:31:44,120 --> 00:31:45,140
It's part of the island

461
00:31:45,390 --> 00:31:49,520
And after I do what it told me... I let
you go... it will become part of me,too

462
00:31:49,920 --> 00:31:50,850
Don't let him take me

463
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:52,570
I don't have a choice

464
00:31:52,910 --> 00:31:54,840
To stay here,I have to
believe that I'm young again

465
00:31:55,370 --> 00:31:57,250
And with you here to remind me,I can't

466
00:31:57,660 --> 00:31:59,960
No,papa,please.Help me

467
00:32:00,020 --> 00:32:01,860
A child can't have a child,Rumple

468
00:32:02,160 --> 00:32:03,280
I'm sorry but it's true

469
00:32:04,560 --> 00:32:05,430
Don't fight it

470
00:32:06,490 --> 00:32:08,280
We both know that you're
better off without me

471
00:32:10,420 --> 00:32:16,180
I was never meant to be a father.No

472
00:32:49,180 --> 00:32:49,990
Hello,laddie

473
00:32:51,280 --> 00:32:52,860
Oh,I see you've come bearing gifts

474
00:32:55,430 --> 00:32:56,490
Where's Henry

475
00:32:56,680 --> 00:32:57,920
Oh,you mean my great-grandson

476
00:32:59,830 --> 00:33:01,840
You still haven't told
the others who I really am

477
00:33:03,730 --> 00:33:04,750
Not even your own son

478
00:33:06,200 --> 00:33:07,000
Why

479
00:33:07,660 --> 00:33:09,530
Because you're nothing
but a coward to me

480
00:33:09,950 --> 00:33:12,870
We both know if that were
true, I'd already be in that box

481
00:33:13,820 --> 00:33:15,150
You don't think I can do it

482
00:33:16,320 --> 00:33:19,840
- You let me inside just to,uh,taunt me.
- No

483
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:25,410
To see you again, to
give you one last chance

484
00:33:26,700 --> 00:33:27,570
Stay with me

485
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:29,690
Let this go

486
00:33:32,340 --> 00:33:33,550
Let's start over

487
00:33:35,170 --> 00:33:36,880
Do you think I want to be with you

488
00:33:38,710 --> 00:33:41,540
That I could ever forgive
you after you abandoned me

489
00:33:42,640 --> 00:33:44,120
I'm disappointed,Rumple

490
00:33:44,840 --> 00:33:47,120
After all these years,I
thought you'd be more...

491
00:33:48,710 --> 00:33:53,970
understanding, considering you
did the same thing to your son

492
00:33:54,580 --> 00:33:59,720
You traded Baelfire for the power of
a dagger, and I traded you for youth

493
00:34:01,020 --> 00:34:02,990
We're a lot more alike
than you care to admit

494
00:34:03,170 --> 00:34:06,010
- We are nothing alike
- Oh,of course we are

495
00:34:06,310 --> 00:34:07,780
And it's nothing to be ashamed of

496
00:34:09,070 --> 00:34:11,530
Neither one of us was cut
out to be a father,m'boy

497
00:34:11,900 --> 00:34:14,910
I regretted leaving my
son the moment I let him go

498
00:34:15,970 --> 00:34:19,190
I spent my life trying to
find him, to get him back

499
00:34:20,450 --> 00:34:21,560
And what did you do

500
00:34:22,290 --> 00:34:23,570
You forgot about me

501
00:34:23,740 --> 00:34:24,900
I never forgot about you

502
00:34:26,220 --> 00:34:28,440
Why do you think I
call myself "Peter Pan"

503
00:34:29,100 --> 00:34:32,410
Don't think for a moment I believe
it's because you care for me

504
00:34:33,350 --> 00:34:34,350
But I do

505
00:34:38,090 --> 00:34:41,920
All you have to do is put down
that box, and you'll see it's true

506
00:34:44,240 --> 00:34:50,370
We can make the fresh start you always
wanted, together, just as we planned

507
00:34:54,710 --> 00:34:56,660
Oh,I'm gonna make a fresh start

508
00:34:59,220 --> 00:35:00,280
Just not with you

509
00:35:13,450 --> 00:35:14,470
I don't understand

510
00:35:14,730 --> 00:35:15,790
'Cause you don't have it

511
00:35:20,100 --> 00:35:22,730
- You switched them 
- Follow the lady

512
00:35:23,420 --> 00:35:24,740
Still having trouble believing

513
00:35:25,300 --> 00:35:28,410
In Neverland,all you have to do
is think of something to have it

514
00:35:29,450 --> 00:35:30,550
Even something fake

515
00:35:31,650 --> 00:35:36,590
But the real one...
Well,let's see what it can do

516
00:35:38,940 --> 00:35:43,040
No.I'm sorry,Rumple

517
00:35:44,020 --> 00:35:45,190
You had your chance

518
00:35:46,620 --> 00:35:47,870
The choice was yours

519
00:36:18,110 --> 00:36:18,900
Come on

520
00:36:23,150 --> 00:36:24,250
What happened to the bean

521
00:36:25,570 --> 00:36:26,550
He used it

522
00:36:27,780 --> 00:36:29,990
He left me and he's never coming back

523
00:36:31,030 --> 00:36:32,450
Oh,it's for the best,Rumple

524
00:36:33,150 --> 00:36:34,070
I'm alone now

525
00:36:34,750 --> 00:36:36,450
No,you have us...
- And a wheel

526
00:36:36,580 --> 00:36:37,720
- You always have a home here

527
00:36:38,490 --> 00:36:40,370
Now get some rest...
And you'll feel better

528
00:36:40,590 --> 00:36:42,050
Later we'll spin,hmm

529
00:36:42,410 --> 00:36:43,300
Where's your doll

530
00:36:44,890 --> 00:36:45,740
I lost him

531
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:47,830
Well,we'll make you another one

532
00:36:49,280 --> 00:36:50,620
You can give it the same name

533
00:36:51,230 --> 00:36:54,770
No.Peter Pan is gone forever

534
00:37:27,500 --> 00:37:28,360
What is this place

535
00:37:29,400 --> 00:37:31,050
I don't remember
seeing it from my dreams

536
00:37:31,340 --> 00:37:33,660
That's because it didn't exist

537
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:37,800
It was created when you made
the decision to stay here

538
00:37:38,050 --> 00:37:39,080
A giant skull

539
00:37:39,710 --> 00:37:40,820
It's glorious

540
00:37:42,420 --> 00:37:43,570
What's the hourglass for

541
00:37:43,740 --> 00:37:46,360
It represents the magic
fueling your youth,

542
00:37:46,540 --> 00:37:50,140
the magic allowing you to
stay here, to stay young

543
00:37:50,780 --> 00:37:52,300
And what happens when it runs out

544
00:37:52,630 --> 00:37:56,850
Your youth will be
taken and you will die

545
00:37:57,710 --> 00:37:59,620
But I thought I was going
to stay young forever

546
00:37:59,770 --> 00:38:02,780
Neverland is a place for
children to visit in their dreams,

547
00:38:02,960 --> 00:38:04,740
not a place for them to live

548
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:06,940
You are the first to try to stay

549
00:38:07,120 --> 00:38:10,390
And in doing so,you're
breaking the rules

550
00:38:10,680 --> 00:38:13,390
Any rule can be broken,especially here

551
00:38:13,770 --> 00:38:16,570
I made this place without
even thinking about it

552
00:38:18,620 --> 00:38:21,090
- There has to be a way.
- Perhaps

553
00:38:21,270 --> 00:38:22,300
Then I will find it

554
00:38:23,300 --> 00:38:24,270
I will find a way

555
00:38:25,860 --> 00:38:26,700
I believe

556
00:38:37,890 --> 00:38:38,780
It's time,Henry

557
00:38:40,050 --> 00:38:43,560
Time to save magic, to save Neverland

558
00:38:44,560 --> 00:38:45,490
What do I have to do

559
00:38:46,130 --> 00:38:49,970
You must give me your heart,Henry...
the heart of the truest believer

560
00:38:51,670 --> 00:38:54,010
You mean... I have to believe

561
00:38:54,660 --> 00:38:55,660
No,Henry

562
00:38:57,800 --> 00:39:00,740
I mean,you need to give me your heart

563
00:39:02,350 --> 00:39:04,300
But... what will happen to me

564
00:39:04,760 --> 00:39:06,900
You'll become the greatest of all heroes

565
00:39:08,480 --> 00:39:09,750
You can tell me the truth

566
00:39:11,010 --> 00:39:13,210
I know all magic comes with a price

567
00:39:13,640 --> 00:39:15,480
Saving it must come with a price,too

568
00:39:15,810 --> 00:39:17,340
I would never lie to you,Henry

569
00:39:18,170 --> 00:39:19,110
I mean,you're right

570
00:39:19,790 --> 00:39:21,310
There is a price

571
00:39:27,320 --> 00:39:30,060
You have to stay here
on the island with me

572
00:39:31,160 --> 00:39:33,000
Neverland will become your new home

573
00:39:34,020 --> 00:39:36,750
I know it's a huge
sacrifice,but isn't it worth it

574
00:39:38,320 --> 00:39:40,290
Heroes have to make
sacrifices all the time

575
00:39:41,180 --> 00:39:42,430
My family taught me that

576
00:39:42,760 --> 00:39:47,280
Then they'd be proud if they could see you
now, because you're about to save them all

577
00:39:50,530 --> 00:39:52,600
- Now are you ready?
- Yes

578
00:39:53,010 --> 00:39:53,810
Then let me help you

579
00:40:11,550 --> 00:40:12,370
Henry,wait

580
00:40:13,340 --> 00:40:14,960
Whatever Pan's telling
you to do,don't do it

581
00:40:15,160 --> 00:40:17,820
- Dad.You're alive?
- I am,buddy

582
00:40:18,510 --> 00:40:19,550
And I need you to listen to me

583
00:40:20,340 --> 00:40:21,430
Pan is lying to you

584
00:40:21,600 --> 00:40:28,310
Oh,pleasure to see you,too,Baelfire, not
to mention the Savior and the Evil Queen

585
00:40:29,520 --> 00:40:31,790
Henry, you need to get away from him now

586
00:40:31,930 --> 00:40:33,540
- He's trying to hurt you
- No

587
00:40:34,010 --> 00:40:35,250
The heart of the truest believer

588
00:40:35,820 --> 00:40:37,280
It's what's gonna save magic

589
00:40:37,920 --> 00:40:39,230
It's gonna save all of you

590
00:40:39,430 --> 00:40:40,520
No,it's not

591
00:40:42,260 --> 00:40:44,180
This was never about magic,Henry

592
00:40:45,060 --> 00:40:46,260
You have to believe us

593
00:40:47,420 --> 00:40:49,980
The only person Pan's
interested in saving is himself

594
00:40:50,160 --> 00:40:50,980
That's not true

595
00:40:51,300 --> 00:40:52,290
Of course it isn't

596
00:40:52,510 --> 00:40:53,290
Yes,it is

597
00:40:54,380 --> 00:40:55,950
Pan can't live without you dying

598
00:40:56,110 --> 00:40:57,740
If you give him your
heart,it's gonna kill you

599
00:40:58,150 --> 00:40:59,850
They're trying to stem your belief,Henry

600
00:40:59,990 --> 00:41:00,850
But don't let them

601
00:41:02,350 --> 00:41:05,000
Remember,every hero gets tested

602
00:41:10,670 --> 00:41:15,330
Henry... I know what being a
hero looks like, and this isn't it

603
00:41:16,640 --> 00:41:17,420
Why would they lie

604
00:41:17,670 --> 00:41:19,820
Because that's what adults do,Henry

605
00:41:21,150 --> 00:41:22,710
You know that better than anyone

606
00:41:24,980 --> 00:41:27,300
Henry... you have to believe us

607
00:41:27,700 --> 00:41:29,850
Your parents don't care
about Neverland,Henry

608
00:41:30,370 --> 00:41:33,360
They know if you give your heart
to save it, then you'll have to stay

609
00:41:35,380 --> 00:41:37,570
They're being selfish because
they don't wanna lose you

610
00:41:38,050 --> 00:41:40,180
- Henry,you have to trust us
- Trust!

611
00:41:41,470 --> 00:41:43,610
I'm the only one who's ever
been honest with you,Henry

612
00:41:44,570 --> 00:41:46,250
The only one who ever believed in you

613
00:41:48,040 --> 00:41:50,700
This is your choice.Not theirs

614
00:41:53,360 --> 00:41:54,480
You have to choose now

615
00:41:55,180 --> 00:41:56,380
We're running out of time

616
00:41:57,710 --> 00:42:00,630
We believe in
you,Henry.Because we love you

617
00:42:01,910 --> 00:42:03,080
More than anything

618
00:42:04,090 --> 00:42:04,930
I love you,too

619
00:42:08,620 --> 00:42:10,030
But I have to save magic

620
00:42:10,230 --> 00:42:11,760
No,no,no,no.I'm sorry

621
00:42:13,180 --> 00:42:14,160
No.

622
00:42:38,290 --> 00:42:39,000
Henry

